                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.51/306: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Price</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-18T09:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1921—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. Supplementing my 103, May 16, 9 a.m. I communicated Department’s telegram
                    46, May 14, 6 p.m., duly Monday morning and followed it up with all possible
                    efforts but Panaman President took the position reported in my cipher telegram
                    103 even more emphatically.</p>
                <p>Contract between the Panaman Government and manager of the Banco Nacional to act
                    as Government depositary for four years was signed Monday afternoon. Late
                    yesterday the directorate approved same.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
